#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc50"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Acelakavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 50"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "50. Uyyodhikasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on battles"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.50.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.379"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1005"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dirattatirattaṃ senāya vasamānā uyyodhikampi balaggampi senābyūhampi anīkadassanampi gacchanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were staying with the army for two or three nights, and they went to see battles, troop reviews, the massing of the army, and troop inspections."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Aññataropi chabbaggiyo bhikkhu uyyodhikaṃ gantvā kaṇḍena paṭividdho hoti."
msgstr "One of the monks who went to a battle was even struck by an arrow."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Manussā taṃ bhikkhuṃ uppaṇḍesuṃ—"
msgstr "People mocked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "“kacci, bhante, suyuddhaṃ ahosi, kati te lakkhāni laddhānī”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerable, we hope you had a good battle. How many targets did you hit?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "So bhikkhu tehi manussehi uppaṇḍiyamāno maṅku ahosi."
msgstr "And because they mocked him, he felt humiliated."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya āgacchissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics go to see a battle?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa kāraṇā uyyodhikaṃ āgacchāmā”ti."
msgstr "It’s our misfortune that we must go to battles for the sake of our livelihood and because of our wives and children.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1006"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya gacchissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six go to see a battle?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya gacchathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.380"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya gacchissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you go to see a battle?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1007"></a>
#. VAR: uyyodhikaṃ → uyyodhakaṃ (s3)
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "“Dirattatirattañce bhikkhu senāya vasamāno uyyodhikaṃ vā balaggaṃ vā senābyūhaṃ vā anīkadassanaṃ vā gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk who is staying with an army for two or three nights goes to a battle, a troop review, a massing of the army, or a troop inspection, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "(<em>50</em>:<strong>99</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.50.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.50.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1008"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Dirattatirattañce bhikkhu senāya vasamānoti"
msgstr "If a monk who is staying with an army for two or three nights:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "dvetisso rattiyo vasamāno."
msgstr "he is staying for two or for three nights."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1009"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Uyyodhikaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A battle:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "yattha sampahāro dissati."
msgstr "wherever fighting is seen."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1010"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Balaggaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A troop review:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "ettakā hatthī, ettakā assā, ettakā rathā, ettakā pattī."
msgstr "so many elephants, so many horses, so many chariots, so much infantry."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1011"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Senābyūhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A massing of the army:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "ito hatthī hontu, ito assā hontu, ito rathā hontu, ito pattikā hontu."
msgstr "let the elephants set out from here; let the horses set out from here; let the chariots set out from here; let the infantry set out from here."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.108"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1012"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Anīkaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Troops:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "hatthānīkaṃ, assānīkaṃ, rathānīkaṃ, pattānīkaṃ."
msgstr "elephant troops, horse  troops, chariot troops, infantry troops."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Tayo hatthī pacchimaṃ hatthānīkaṃ, tayo assā pacchimaṃ assānīkaṃ, tayo rathā pacchimaṃ rathānīkaṃ, cattāro purisā sarahatthā pattī pacchimaṃ pattānīkaṃ."
msgstr "The smallest unit of elephants is three elephants; the smallest unit of horses is three horses; the smallest unit of chariots is three chariots; the smallest unit of infantry is four men with arrows in hand."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is on his way to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "Every time he moves outside of the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1013"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Ekamekaṃ dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is on his way to see one division of a fourfold army, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "Every time he moves outside of the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.50.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1014"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "ārāme ṭhito passati,"
msgstr "if he sees it while standing in the monastery;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "bhikkhussa ṭhitokāsaṃ vā nisinnokāsaṃ vā nipannokāsaṃ vā āgantvā sampahāro dissati,"
msgstr "if the army comes to where the monk happens to be standing, sitting, or lying down, and he then sees fighting;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.381"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "paṭipathaṃ gacchanto passati,"
msgstr "if he sees it while walking in the opposite direction;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "sati karaṇīye gantvā passati,"
msgstr "if he goes because there is something to be done, and he then sees it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1015"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "Uyyodhikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on battles, is finished."

#. </p><p class="endchapter">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "Acelakavaggo pañcamo."
msgstr "The fifth chapter on naked ascetics is finished."

#. </p><p class="endsection summary"><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1016"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. </p><div class="uddana"><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1017"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid "Pūvaṃ kathopanandassa,"
msgstr "Biscuit, talk, three on Upananda,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "tayaṃpaṭṭhākameva ca;"
msgstr "And even the supporter;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.14"
msgid "Mahānāmo pasenadi,"
msgstr "Mahānāma, Pasenadi,"

#. <br> 
#. VAR: senāviddho ime dasāti → uyyuttaṃ senuy­yodhi­kanti (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc50:pts-cs2.2.15"
msgid "senāviddho ime dasāti."
msgstr "Army, and struck: those are the ten."

